		<div id="unique-entry-id-69" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="24b816fa2b7025a7192910a635992334-69.php" class="blog-permalink">GtkAda contributions v3.9</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-17 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><br />Changes to the version 3.29 :<br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>Compatibility functions Get_Iter_At_Location and Get_Iter_At_Position were added to the package Gtk.Missed. </li><li>The functions provide backward compatibility to GTK 3.14 to 3.19 when the GTK interface was changed. </li><li>The implementation works with both earlier and later versions.</li></ul><br />Changes to this version 5.15 : <br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GNAT Studio Community 2021 bugs worked around; </li><li>GTK 3.24.x support</li></ul><br /><br />See <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions.htm" target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web page</a> for details<br /><br />Download from <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/gtkadacontributions/files/latest/download " target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">SourceForge</a><br />Download source <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz" target="_blank" title="gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz" download="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz">gtkada_contributions_3_30.tgz</a> from <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/gtkada_contributions.htm" target="_blank" title="GtkAda contributions">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web</a><br /><br /><br /><br />&copy; dmitry-kazakov<br />GPL-2.0-or-later<br /><br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="24b816fa2b7025a7192910a635992334-69.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-gtk.php" title="GTK" rel="tag">GTK</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-68" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="e0fbf66e17d4118737c3726106d77511-68.php" class="blog-permalink">Fuzzy sets library v5.15</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-17 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><br />Changes to this version 5.15 : <br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GNAT Studio Community 2021 bugs worked around; </li><li>GTK 3.24.x support</li></ul><br /><br />See <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy.htm" target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web page</a> for details<br /><br />Download from <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/fuzzysetsforada/files/latest/download " target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">SourceForge</a><br />Download source <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_5_15.tgz" target="_blank" title="components_4_61.tgz" download="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_5_15.tgz">fuzzy_5_15.tgz</a> from <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy.htm" target="_blank" title="Fuzzy sets for Ada">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web</a><br /><br /><br /><br />&copy; dmitry-kazakov<br />GPL-2.0-or-later<br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="e0fbf66e17d4118737c3726106d77511-68.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-ml.php" title="ML" rel="tag">ML</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-65" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="4ed90bba4e1688deb9ebf849881936d0-65.php" class="blog-permalink">FUZZY v1.12</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-17 </div><div class="blog-entry-body">Fuzzy machine learning framework is a library and a GUI front-end for machine learning using intuitionistic fuzzy data. <br /><br />Changes in the version 1.10<br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GNAT Studio Community 2021 bugs worked around;</li><li>GTK 3.24.x support.</li></ul><br /><br />See <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_ml.htm" target="_blank" title="Fuzzy ML">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web page</a> for details<br /><br />Download from <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/fuzzyml/files/latest/download " target="_blank" title="units_3_9">SourceForge</a><br />Download sources <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_ml_1_12.tgz" target="_blank" title="fuzzy_ml_1_12.tgz" download="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_ml_1_12.tgz">fuzzy_ml_1_12.tgz</a> from <a href="http://www.dmitry-kazakov.de/ada/fuzzy_ml.htm" target="_blank" title="Units of measurement for Ada">Dmitry&rsquo;s Web</a><br /><br /><br />&copy; dmitry-kazakov<br />GPL-2.0-or-later<br /><br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="4ed90bba4e1688deb9ebf849881936d0-65.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-ml.php" title="ML" rel="tag">ML</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-62" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="8f13744be838d4731bbd5099e2a32555-62.php" class="blog-permalink">Qt 6.3 bindings</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-04-13 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><br />Based on <a href="https://www.qt.io/blog/qt-6.3-released" target="_blank" title="Qt released">Qt-6.3.0-everywhere</a> opensource <br /><br />built with <br /><ul class="disc"><li>Microsoft Visual Studio 2019 x64 Windows</li><li>gcc amd64 in Linux</li></ul><br />Package tested with <br /><ul class="disc"><li>gnat gpl 2020 ada compiler in Windows 64bit , </li><li>gnat gpl 2020 Linux amd64 Debian 11.1 </li></ul><br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li><span style="font:12px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#434343;">Qt6Ada (Ada-2020 port to Qt 6.3.0 extended (qtgraphicaleffects qtgamepad qtspeech qtx11extras qtwinextras)</span></li><ul class="dashed"><li><span style="font:12px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#EF1216;"><u><a href="https://r3fowwcolhrzycn2yzlzzw.on.drv.tw/AdaStudio/qt6ada/qt6ada.html">Qt6Ada</a></u></span><span style="font:12px Arial, Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif; color:#434343;">. release 12.04.2022</span></li></ul></ul><br />See also <a href="https://r3fowwcolhrzycn2yzlzzw-on.drv.tw/AdaStudio/index.html" target="_blank" title="AdaStudio">AdaStudio WebPage</a>   <br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="8f13744be838d4731bbd5099e2a32555-62.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-qt.php" title="QT" rel="tag">QT</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-64" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="deef5c6ca812855625106adba30c4a7d-64.php" class="blog-permalink">GNOGA 2.1a released</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-03-06 </div><div class="blog-entry-body">GNOGA is a framework for building portable apps:<br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>Communication platform between the Ada code and the browser / native</li><li>Binding to the HTML5 DOM and Browser</li><li>Application start up services</li><li>High level containers and GUI widgets</li><li>Client side application APIs</li><li>Database bindings and server side APIs (MySQL, SQLite 3)</li><li>development tools</li><li>Plugin bindings to existing JavaScript libraries (jQuery, jQueryUI, Boot_Strap, Messages_Boxes, Menu, Tree, &hellip;</li><li>Native Desktop and Mobile Application Support coming (GTK)</li></ul><br /><br />&copy; David Botton<br />Sources :<br />Runtime : LGPL-3.0-or-later<br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="deef5c6ca812855625106adba30c4a7d-64.php"> Read More…</a></span></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-54" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="7a4ac44684893632ee14e6b0587c3c64-54.php" class="blog-permalink">GWindows release v2022-01-29</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2022-01-29 </div><div class="blog-entry-body">GWindows is a full Microsoft Windows <strong>Rapid Application Development</strong> framework for programming GUIs (Graphical User Interfaces) with Ada. <br /><br />GWindows works only with the GNAT development system, but with some effort, GWindows could be made pure Ada. <br />GWindows is free and open-source! <br /><br />Changes to the framework are detailed in <a href="https://sourceforge.net/p/gnavi/code/HEAD/tree/gwindows/changes.txt" target="_blank">gwindows/changes.txt</a> or in the News forum on the <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/gnavi/" target="_blank">project site</a>. <br /><br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="7a4ac44684893632ee14e6b0587c3c64-54.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-windows.php" title="Windows" rel="tag">Windows</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-15" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="72d029dd42d1dda293ced93099b935db-15.php" class="blog-permalink">Muen microkernel 0.7 relesaed</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2016-02-22 </div><div class="blog-entry-body">The <a href="http://muen.codelabs.ch/" rel="external">Muen Separation Kernel</a> is the world&rsquo;s first Open Source microkernel that has been formally proven to contain no runtime errors at the source code level. It is developed in Switzerland by the Institute for Internet Technologies and Applications (ITA) at the University of Applied Sciences Rapperswil (HSR).<br /><br />The following major features and improvements have been implemented :<br /><ul class="disc"><li>Support for <a href="http://genode-labs.com/" rel="external">Genode VM</a> subjects</li><li>Subject time mechanism</li><li>Hardware and platform policy abstractions</li><li>Linux virtual filesystem and network interface drivers</li></ul><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="72d029dd42d1dda293ced93099b935db-15.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-linux.php" title="Linux" rel="tag">Linux</a>,<a href="tag-spark.php" title="SPARK" rel="tag">SPARK</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-14" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="6ea470c775774350d81dfaa1c7da7c57-14.php" class="blog-permalink">XNAdaLib 2015 binaries for MacOS 10.9 including GTKAda GPL 2015 and more</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2015-09-03 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">This is XNAdaLib 2015 built on MacOS 10.9 Mavericks for Native Quartz including:<br /></span><ul class="disc"><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">GTK Ada GPL 2015 with GTK+ 3.16.0 complete,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">Glade 3.18.3,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">GnatColl GPL 2015,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">Florist GPL 2015,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">AdaCurses 20110404,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">Gate 3-04-b,</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">AICWL 3.11 (with Components 4.8 and gtksourceview 3.14.3),</span></li><li><span style="font:14px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">GNOGA 1.1a,</span></li></ul><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="6ea470c775774350d81dfaa1c7da7c57-14.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-osx.php" title="OSX" rel="tag">OSX</a>,<a href="tag-quartz.php" title="Quartz" rel="tag">Quartz</a>,<a href="tag-gtk.php" title="GTK" rel="tag">GTK</a>,<a href="tag-gnat.php" title="GNAT" rel="tag">GNAT</a>,<a href="tag-macos.php" title="MacOS" rel="tag">MacOS</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-8" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="29d84545ce729f4cfc6916a0e0411242-8.php" class="blog-permalink">Qt5Ada version 5.5.0 released</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2015-07-03 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><span style="font:12px .AppleSystemUIFont; ">Qt5Ada is a Ada-2012 port to Qt5 framework (based on Qt 5.5.0 final)<br /><br />This project uses a proprietary layer. It is not completely open source. (Ref David Botton)</span><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="29d84545ce729f4cfc6916a0e0411242-8.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-qt.php" title="QT" rel="tag">QT</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-0" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="c0f4970b82f198d94b82e96668df5180-0.php" class="blog-permalink">GNOGA v1.1a released</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2015-07-03 </div><div class="blog-entry-body"><span style="font-size:13px; color:#424242;">Gnoga uses modern web technologies to allow simple creation of cross platform GUIs for Ada with native or custom look and feels that perform on par to native toolsets locally and can be easily and securely remoted as web apps over the internet as well.<br /></span><br />In addition to bug fixes and vastly increased stability adds:<br /><ul class="disc"><li>Completed multimedia bindings</li><li>Easier boot file creation by just including boot.js in any html file</li><li>Direct HTTPS and Secure Websockets</li><li>HTTP polling with Ajax including fallback support (using auto.html bootfile)</li></ul><br />Download <a href="http://www.gnoga.com/gnoga-1.1a.zip" rel="external">gnoga-v1.1a.zip</a> <br />or<br /><code>git clone git://git.code.sf.net/p/gnoga/code gnoga</code>or<br /><code>git refresh ; git stash; git merge</code><br />or go to <a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/gnoga/" rel="external">SourceForge</a><br /><br /><ul class="disc"><li>GPLv3 license with Runtime Exceptions.</li></ul>From David Botton<br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="c0f4970b82f198d94b82e96668df5180-0.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-web.php" title="Web" rel="tag">Web</a>,<a href="tag-javascript.php" title="JavaScript" rel="tag">JavaScript</a></p></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-2" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title"><a href="375eef2f7cb297bece84c6a0ea0a649d-2.php" class="blog-permalink">Matreshka 0.7.0 Released</a></h1><div class="blog-entry-date">2015-05-22 </div><div class="blog-entry-body">We are pleased to announce new major release of <a href="http://forge.ada-ru.org/matreshka" rel="external">Matreshka</a>. See <a href="http://forge.ada-ru.org/matreshka/wiki/ReleaseNotes/0.7" rel="external">Release Notes</a> for more information and visit <a href="http://forge.ada-ru.org/matreshka/wiki/Download" rel="external">Download</a> to download source code and binary packages.<br /><span class="blog-read-more"><a href="375eef2f7cb297bece84c6a0ea0a649d-2.php"> Read More…</a></span><p class="blog-entry-tags">Tags: <a href="tag-database.php" title="Database" rel="tag">Database</a>,<a href="tag-sql.php" title="SQL" rel="tag">SQL</a></p></div></div>
